1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e3 Nf6 4. Bxc4 e6 5. Nf3 c5 6. Qe2
{ This move tries to avoid the mainlines. It is a little bit tricky, as White immediately plans to take on c5, and then play O-O-Rd1/e4. I believe it is worth knowing how to handle a sideline like this. }
6... a6
{ Placing the pawn on a6 is always good in the QGA opening, because it will help Black to develop its pieces. }
7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. O-O
{ White castles and gets ready for the middlegame plans with e4/Rd1. } 8...
Nbd7
