1. d4 d5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bf4
{ This move was picked up by Rapport and Jobova a few years back and it has been quite popular since then. White's main idea oftentimes is to quickly develop the queenside pieces and go for the long castle. }
3... c5 4. dxc5 { Grabbing the pawn would lead to consequences for White. }
4... d4 { Forcing White to retreat the knight. } 5. Nb1 e6 6. Nf3 Bxc5
{ Black is better because White has lost two tempi with 2. Nc3 and 5. Nb1. The d4-pawn makes it hard for White to develop their pieces. Next is ...Nc6 and ...O-O. }
