6... e6 7. Nf3 cxd4
{ A very typical way to fix the pawn structure for the long term. } 8. exd4 Nc6
{ Black now has a healthy position with the bishop-pair. White still needs to solve the issue with the knight on c3. Black's plans are the following: Bd7, Qb6, O-O-O, or Bd7, a6, Qc7, O-O-O, Bd6, h5-h4, Rg8. }
