13. Re1 g5
{ The following plan will target the d4-pawn: Bg7-Ng8-Ne7. Since the position is closed, Black has time to maneuver. }
14. f3 Ng8 15. e4 Ne7
{ The position is roughly equal. But personally, I prefer Black in the long run, since White's center can easily collapse. Black's plan is the following: ...Bg7, O-O and if White plays e5 then usually the fast f6-breakthrough is the right response. }
