Qa3
{ This pin is the core idea of the opening. White has a simple target, which is the c5-pawn or square. Black has to solve this problem. }
10... Ne4
{ A very logical move that protects both the queen and the pawn. Now, White's only good plan is to exchange the black piece that holds Black's center together. }
11. Nfd2 e5
{ Once, one of my good friends, Zoltan Almasi who is one of the best chess players in the world taught me that I should always check what squares my opponent no longer controls after each move. Now, we can see that with @@StartFEN@@r1b2rk1/p4ppp/2pqp3/2pp4/3Pn3/Q1P1PN2/PP3PPP/RN2K2R w KQ - 4 11@@EndFEN@@  11.Nfd2  , White no longer has jurisdiction over the e5-square. This move's main idea is that it opens the way for the Black queen to go to g6, which will put pressure on White's kingside. }
12. Nxe4 dxe4 13. Qxc5
{ 13.dxc5?  This would leave the a3-queen excluded.  13...Qg6  The white kingside becomes too weak, and the Black queen becomes too powerful. White has to deal with the g2-pawn now. }
13... Qg6
{ Now we can see that White's disadvantage in development is showing. Black is threatening to take on g2. However, White is pretty much forced to give up the pawn, since they should solve their development first. }
14. Nd2
{ 14.g3  Ba6⩱  Black has a great deal of compensation. Next is ...exd4 and then ...Bd3 will make White's position very unpleasant. }
14... Qxg2 15. O-O-O
{ This is the best option for White. Now the white king is safe and a lot of Black pawns are under attack. }
15... Qxf2
{ Black has to collect one pawn. Now Black is also threatening to take another one on e3. }
16. Qxe5
{ White tries to capture the pawns back in a way that their pawn structure would remain healthy. However, now the e3-pawn is not protected. }
16... Qxe3
{ Black is taking a pawn and waiting for White to show compensation. } 17. Qxe4
{ Exchanging the queens would lead White to a slightly worse endgame. } 17...
Qxe4 18. Nxe4 f5 19. Nc5 g5
{ Black has a comfortable endgame with a simple plan of pushing the passed pawns. }
