{ Putting the rook on the open file is almost always a good idea. It also threatens ...Rb5 to target the e5-pawn. }
17. Nc4
{ The white knight on c4 is ideally placed. Therefore Black has to bother this knight. }
17... Be6 { Trying to get rid of the knight on c4. } 18. Rd2
{ The only move to keep the game balanced. } 18... Qf3
{ Attacking the rook with a tempo. } 19. Re1
{ White has to protect the e3-pawn. } 19... Bxc4 20. Qxc4 Rbd8
{ This position is roughly equal, but both sides have to play good moves to not be worse. Black has to keep chasing the weak pawns on h2, e3, e5 and try to keep the d-file under control. }
