4... e5
{ A very important move. Black immediately attacks the strangely placed knight on a3. }
5. Nxe5
{ The best option for White.  5.Nxc4?  looks logical but surprisingly, Black is much better here  5...e4!  6.Nfe5  b5∓  The knights cannot coordinate well, therefore eventually White will lose material.   5.dxe5  Qxd1+  6.Kxd1  Ne4∓  with a very nice endgame for Black. }
5... Bxa3 { The cleanest way to get an advantage. } 6. bxa3 b5
{ Usually, in the Queen's Gambit Accepted, the c4-pawn is a weakness, however here it is an asset. }
7. e3 a6
{ Black has a very stable position and is better. The plan is the following: ...Bb7, ...O-O, and ...Nbd7. }
