5. e4
{ Occupying the center immediately. I believe that this is the most dangerous move that White could make. The following moves might remind you of @@StartBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.d4  d5  2.c4  c6  3.Nf3  Nf6  4.Nc3  dxc4  5.a4  e6  6.e4  Bb4  7.e5  Nd5  @@EndBracket@@  . It is very important to remember the exact move order, otherwise Black will have problems. }
