{ Black has to keep the strong pawn structure as long as White lets us. Now, White has three moves that I consider playable.  5.axb5  which is the mainline,  5.Nc3  , and  5.b3  . I will cover all the moves, but I believe that the critical move is  5.axb5  . }
5. Nc3 { Putting pressure on the b5-pawn. } 5... b4
{ I think this is the best move for Black. This position will go into an interesting middlegame which is worth studying with both colors. Now White has several alternatives with the knight. }
6. Nce2
{ I believe that this is the trickiest line of all the knight moves, but not the best. White wants to transfer the knight to g3, so it potentially could create an attack on the kingside later in the middlegame. }
6... e6
{ An important move which immediately threatens to break the white center with ...c5. }
7. Ng3 Ba6
{ Black has to defend the c4-pawn first, and then break the center with ...c5. }
8. Nf3 c5
{ Black is a pawn up, and that is why opening the position in the center is a good idea. I believe that White has several logical moves here, and I will cover them all. }
9. d5
{ A very typical way to keep tension in the center. White could create a great attack if Black does not respond well to this. }
9... exd5
{ I think it is important to keep the position as simple as possible for Black. }
10. exd5 Nf6 { Putting pressure on the d5-pawn. } 11. Bg5
{ White is sacrificing another pawn to get good compensation. } 11... Qxd5 12.
Qxd5 Nxd5
{ Black has accepted the pawn sacrifice, and is two pawns up. However, White's next move will shake Black's position. }
13. O-O-O { Castling with a tempo, which forces Black to play only moves. }
13... h6 { The only move that saves the game. } 14. Re1+
{ White has to make sure that the Black king cannot castle in the near future. }
14... Kd7
{ It seems that Black walked into a scary check on e5. But now, Black is sacrificing one pawn back to get some development in exchange. }
15. Ne5+ Kc7 16. Nxf7 Rg8 17. Bd8+ Kb7 18. Be2
{ Black's position is not fun to have, with their exposed king and uncoordinated pieces. }
