{ This is the main idea of 8...b3, as now White has to waste time defending the pawn on e4. }
12. f3
{ Now White made its position very stable and wants to develop with Be3-Nd2-Rc1 which would target the c4-pawn. Therefore Black has to act fast to prevent the queenside from collapsing. }
12... Nfd7
{ A very important move that gives great ideas for Black. The main idea is ...Ne5 to protect the c4-pawn. }
13. Be3 Ne5 14. Nd2
{ White is simply developing and asking whether Black will protect the pawn on c4 after White plays Rc1. }
14... Bb4 { A very healthy developing move that pins the knight as well. } 15.
Rc1 Nbd7
{ Now Black wants to take the opportunity to play ...Nc5-Nd3 which would give a great advantage, White cannot let that happen. }
16. Nxb3
{ It looks like White has just taken a very important pawn, and thus equalized the material, but it gives time for Black to take the initiative. }
16... Rd8
{ The position favors Black, since the White pieces are not well-coordinated, and Black is more developed. }
