{ I think an important idea is to remember to keep the queens on the board here. I believe that  6...Qxd1  would go into a slightly worse endgame, which could be a little unpleasant to hold. Therefore I suggest keeping the tension more by not trading queens for now. }
6... Bb4+ 7. Bd2 Bc5
{ With 6...Bb4, Black managed to chase the bishop to a worse square. First, Black is threatening with ...Qd4, secondly, White cannot trade queens. }
8. Nf3 Ne7 { Disregarding the fact that the pawn on c4 is under attack. } 9.
bxc4 { This would allow Black to have a very nice pawn structures after - }
9... b4
{ Black is better since the pawn on b4 will be a great asset for the rest of the game, and the e5-pawn will most likely fall later on. }
