[Black "6.Nc3 Qb6 7.Be2 e6 #1|Informational 8...Bb7"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 b5 4. a4 c6 5. axb5 cxb5 6. Nc3 Qb6 7. Be2
{ This move has been recently played by a very strong super GM, Jan-Krzysztof Duda. Its idea is that when Black plays ...e6, then the White knight can be developed to h3, which will lead to a very creative position. }
7... e6 { Black stops White from playing Nd5 for the rest of the game. } 8. Nh3
{ This move may seem odd at first, as it is quite unusual to develop the knight to h3, but it is a very creative move. The h3-knight can oftentimes go to f4 which will help White to play d5 with more strength. }
8... Bb7
{ Sergey Karjakin has played this move, but I believe that he was not really familiar with this whole Be2-Nh3 idea, therefore he had to come up with moves without the help of the engine. I have to add that Bb7 does seem like a very logical move, but I believe it is not the best. }
9. O-O Nf6 10. Be3 { White threatens d5, which looks concerning for Black. }
10... Nxe4 11. Nxe4 Bxe4 12. d5 { White has a crushing attack here. } *

