{ Immediately highlighting the fact that the e4-pawn has no defender. The following moves are quite forced for both colors. There is no room for making inaccurate moves. }
11. Na4 Nxe4 { Black grabs the pawn and also plans to develop its f8-bishop. }
12. Bxc4 Bxd6 13. Ng5
{ This is the key idea of the move @@StartFEN@@rnb1kb1r/pq3ppp/4pn2/1p1P4/2p1P3/2N1BN2/1P3PPP/R2QKB1R w KQkq - 1 10@@EndFEN@@  10.d6  . If there was no Ng5, then White would simply be down in material without much compensation. Now Black is the one who has to play accurately to keep the position balanced. }
