{ White castles and gets ready for the middlegame plans with e4/Rd1.   8.e4  b5!  Wins a tempo and gives Black some squares to develop its pieces.  9.Bd3  Nbd7  10.O-O  White has nothing better than to transpose to the mainline. This transposes to @@StartFEN@@rnbqk2r/1p3ppp/p3pn2/2b5/2B5/4PN2/PP2QPPP/RNB1K2R w KQkq - 0 8@@EndFEN@@  8.O-O  Nbd7  9.e4  b5  10.Bd3  . }
8... Nbd7
{ There are other alternatives for Black instead of this move, but I believe the knight belongs on d7, as it keeps Black's position flexible. One of the benefits of this move is that White can no longer play Rd1 with a tempo. }
9. Rd1
{ This move would be not so effective because it does not win a tempo, and therefore Black can conveniently develop their pieces. }
9... b5 10. Bd3 Bb7 { Black is totally fine here. Next is ...O-O. } *

