{ I believe this move is the only move that questions Black. Now the a6-b5 pawns are under pressure. }
22... Rxc1+ 23. Bxc1 a5
{ Not the only way to equalize, but I think the easiest. } 24. Bxd5 exd5 25. a4
{ White tries to claim that the a5-pawn will be a long-term target, which is true, but one weakness will not guarantee an advantage. }
25... bxa4 26. bxa4 f5
{ This endgame is equal. Black can simply walk their king to e6, and protect the a5-pawn with ...Bd8 if necessary. }
