{ Black has to develop, otherwise, the position would become one-sided. } 16.
Qxd5 { White decides to trade the queens with the hopes of a better endgame. }
16... exd5 17. Rd1 Ne6
{ The position may seem a little bit bad for Black at first since there are two pawns hanging, but Black is doing fine here. The bishop pair gives Black full compensation for material disadvantage in the near future. Also, If White decides to grab a pawn that means that it has to spend extra moves keeping it, which will lead to a position where Black has the development advantage. The best response to  18.Nxb7  is  18...Bc7  . }
