8... Be7 { Black simply develops, waiting for White to start their plan. } 9.
e4
{ There are no other real alternatives for White here other than the obvious e4. Any other move would not create threats towards Black. }
9... b5
{ A novelty! No one played this move before, because it looks a little bit scary, as it gives White the opportunity to open the position with d5 before Black could even castle. However, the concrete moves confirm that Black has nothing to be afraid of here. }
