15. Nd2
{ Transferring the knight to c4 may look logical, but it's slightly slow and gives Black time to conveniently finish development. Also, note that the white king can become vulnerable. }
15... O-O 16. Nc4 Bc7
{ The two bishops are excellently placed and they put pressure on the white king. }
17. b3 Ne5
{ Exchanging the well-placed knight on c4 benefits Black a great deal. Black is better because of the follow-up attack on the white kingside. Next is ...Qg5 or ...Qh4. }
