15... Rd8
{ Bringing the rook into play immediately, as it can bother the white queen. }
16. Bc4
{ The position would become very forced if White decides to attack the queen on e6. }
16... Bxf3
{ The only move that saves the queen, as moving the e6-queen is not an option. }
17. Qd3
{ White has to make this spectacular only move to keep the game balanced, otherwise Black would simply be winning. }
17... Nxe5
{ All the pieces are hanging now! Black has to keep attacking the white queen. }
18. Qxd8+ { The only move that does not lose material. } 18... Kxd8 19. Bxe6
fxe6 20. gxf3 Nxf3+ 21. Kg2 Nd4
{ Black has excellent compensation for the exchange. The d4-knight is powerful, as it puts pressure on the b3-pawn. Next is ...Be7-Bf6-Kd7-Rc8. }
