19. Be3 { Blocking the c5-bishop's diagonal. } 19... exd4 20. Bxd4 Bxd4+ 21.
Rxd4 Ne5
{ This endgame is roughly equal with chances for both sides, however, I believe that Black has nothing to worry about because of the e5-knight. An interesting follow-up move is ...Rh6, which keeps the king in the center and also brings the h8-rook into play. }
