{ This is one of those positions where Black's best option is to develop the knight on c6 because ...Nbd7 would be slightly slow. }
11. Nb3 Bb4
{ A key move. Black wants White to play a3 so the knight on b3 would be unstable later on. }
12. a3 Bd6 13. Nc3 e5
{ Now we can see why 11...Bb4 is a very important detail in this line since Black's next move ...Be6 will win an important tempo. The position is equal with chances for both sides. }
