1. d4 Nf6 2. Nf3 d5 3. c4 dxc4 4. e3 e6 5. Bxc4 c5 6. O-O a6 7. Qe2
{ One of the mainlines. White intends to play Rd1. } 7... b5 8. Bd3 Nc6
{ 8...Nbd7  I suggest that you develop the knight to d7 because it is more stable. I explain this position in more detail in the 7.Qe2 chapter. }
9. a4 { This leads to a sharp position. } 9... bxa4
{ 9...c4  10.Bc2  Bb7  Is worth considering. } 10. Rd1
{ Logically bringing the rook into play. Now Black has to play accurately. }
10... cxd4 11. Rxa4 { 11.Nxd4  Nxd4  12.exd4  Be7=  Black would be fine here. }
11... Nb4
{ A very ambitious move. Black intends to capture White bishop on d3.   11...Be7  12.Nxd4  Nxd4  13.Rxd4  Qb6=  Would have been the more solid choice. Next is castle and Black is fine. }
12. Nxd4 Bd7
{ 12...Nxd3  Would have been slightly more accurate.  13.Rxd3  Bd7  14.Rc4  Rc8=  . }
13. Ra3 e5
{ A creative move.  13...Nxd3  14.Raxd3⩲  . This is why @@StartFEN@@r1bqkb1r/5ppp/p3pn2/8/Rn1N4/3BP3/1P2QPPP/1NBR2K1 b kq - 0 12@@EndFEN@@  12...Nxd3  would have been better. }
14. Nf5 Qc8
{ The position is very complex since it feels like everything is under attack. White could actually be better with accurate moves. }
15. Rc3
{ 15.e4↑  White would have a pretty comfortable attack against the underdeveloped Black pieces. }
15... Qb7 16. e4 Nxd3 17. Qxd3
{ 17.Rcxd3!  Bb5  18.Bg5!  Would have kept the advantage. } 17... Qxe4
{ 17...Nxe4!  Black could have taken over the driver's seat.  18.Rb3  Qc6  19.Rb6  Nxf2∓  I believe Wesley missed this tactic and that is why he did not go for it. }
18. Nd6+ Bxd6 19. Qxd6 Qxb1
{ The best chance is to take the material and hope that the position holds together. }
20. Rc7
{ 20.Rc5+-  This move would have been fatal. The Black king is in serious trouble here. }
20... Qf5
{ A very important defensive move. The position turned again, and White is having trouble proving its compensation. }
21. Re1 e4
{ 21...Ng4!  The best defense is to attack!  22.f3  Qe6⩱  Black would be slightly better. }
22. Bg5
{ 22.Rc5!  Again, this move would have led to a winning attack for White. }
22... Qxg5 23. Rxe4+ Kd8 { Surprisingly enough the Black king on d8 is safe. }
24. Re5 Re8 { White resigned due to the weak last rank. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
